<p><strong>Bug A</strong> — This shop line should show the <strong>axe</strong> with <strong>its own</strong> price. Right now it shows the axe's name but the dagger's price.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">names = [&quot;dagger&quot;, &quot;axe&quot;, &quot;spear&quot;]
price = [10, 40, 25]
game.say(f&quot;{names[1]} costs {price[0]} gold&quot;)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> the name and the price should share the same index.</p>
